---
/**
 * Maricopa Personal Injury Attorneys — Location Page
 * New office (March 2026). SR-347/I-10 interchange. Pinal County.
 */

import PracticeAreaLayout from '../layouts/PracticeAreaLayout.astro';
import { getLocalBusinessSchema } from '../utils/schema';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'Does AZ Law Now have an office in Maricopa?',
    answer: 'Yes. We opened our Maricopa office in March 2026 to better serve Pinal County residents. You can meet with our team locally instead of driving to Phoenix or Buckeye for your consultation.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How long do I have to file an injury claim in Maricopa, Arizona?',
    answer: 'Arizona gives you two years from the date of injury to file a personal injury lawsuit. This applies whether your crash happened on SR-347, John Wayne Parkway, or anywhere in Pinal County. Don\'t wait until the deadline approaches. Evidence disappears and witnesses forget.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What happens if my crash occurred on SR-347 between Maricopa and I-10?',
    answer: 'SR-347 crashes are some of the most dangerous in Pinal County because of the speed, truck traffic, and limited lighting. We\'ve handled multiple cases along this corridor. Brendan investigates the scene, pulls traffic camera footage when available, and documents road conditions that may have contributed to the crash.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Do Maricopa injury cases go through Pinal County courts?',
    answer: 'Most do, yes. Maricopa (the city) sits in Pinal County, so your case would typically be filed in Pinal County Superior Court in Florence. Our litigation team files there regularly and knows the local procedures.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How much does a personal injury attorney cost in Maricopa?',
    answer: 'Zero upfront. We handle all personal injury cases on contingency. You pay nothing unless we recover money for you. No hourly billing, no retainer, no hidden fees.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What if the insurance company already contacted me after my Maricopa crash?',
    answer: 'Don\'t give them a recorded statement. Insurance adjusters contact you quickly because they want to settle cheap, before you know the full extent of your injuries. Call us first. We\'ll handle the insurance company so you can focus on recovering.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can you handle truck crash cases on I-10 near Maricopa?',
    answer: 'Absolutely. Truck crashes involve federal regulations, multiple liable parties, and commercial insurance policies. Brandon Millam handles the litigation side while Brendan investigates the trucking company\'s maintenance records, driver logs, and compliance history. These cases require that level of detail.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How quickly can I get a consultation at the Maricopa office?',
    answer: 'Most Maricopa residents can get a same-day or next-day appointment. If you can\'t come to us, we\'ll come to you. Call (602) 654-0202 to schedule.',
  },
];

const localSchema = getLocalBusinessSchema('Maricopa', 'maricopa');
---

<PracticeAreaLayout
  title="Maricopa Personal Injury Attorneys"
  description="Maricopa injury attorneys at AZ Law Now. New Pinal County office open now. SR-347 and I-10 crash cases. Free consultation. Call (602) 654-0202."
  canonical="/maricopa/"
  practiceArea="Maricopa Personal Injury Attorneys"
  heroTitle="Maricopa Injury Attorneys. Now in Pinal County."
  heroSubtitle="Our new Maricopa office brings the full AZ Law Now team to Pinal County. Same investigator-first approach. Closer to home."
  heroImage="/images/heroes/maricopa.webp"
  faqs={faqs}
  schema={localSchema}
>
  <p>
    Maricopa residents used to drive 45 minutes to meet with an attorney. That's over. We opened our Maricopa office in March 2026 because too many people in Pinal County were settling for less simply because the good firms felt too far away.
  </p>

  <p>
    Now you can sit across the table from Brendan, Brandon, or Stephanie without leaving town. Same team. Same investigation-first approach. Just closer to where you live.
  </p>

  <h2>Why Maricopa Needed a Dedicated Injury Firm</h2>

  <p>
    The city of Maricopa sits at a crossroads. Literally. SR-347 connects the community to I-10, and that stretch of highway is one of the most dangerous corridors in Pinal County. High speeds, semi-truck traffic, limited lighting, and a two-lane road that wasn't built for current traffic volumes create conditions that lead to serious crashes.
  </p>

  <p>
    John Wayne Parkway through town carries increasing local traffic as the population grows. Intersection crashes at Honeycutt Road, Smith-Enke Road, and Maricopa-Casa Grande Highway are becoming more frequent. Residents deserve an injury firm that knows these roads.
  </p>

  <h2>Pinal County Court Experience</h2>

  <p>
    Maricopa injury claims fall under Pinal County Superior Court in Florence. Our litigation team files there regularly. We know the judges, the clerk procedures, and the typical timelines for Pinal County cases. That familiarity means fewer surprises and smoother proceedings.
  </p>

  <p>
    Some Phoenix firms will take your case but rarely set foot in Florence. We're different. Brandon Millam handles Pinal County litigation personally.
  </p>

  <h2>The SR-347 Corridor Problem</h2>

  <p>
    If you commute between Maricopa and the Phoenix metro, you know SR-347. You also know how dangerous it is. The road handles far more traffic than it was designed for, and the interchange at I-10 creates merging hazards that lead to rear-end and sideswipe crashes daily.
  </p>

  <p>
    We've handled cases along this exact corridor. Brendan knows where to find traffic camera footage, how to document road conditions, and which engineering factors contribute to crashes at specific points along SR-347.
  </p>

  <h2>How Our Trio Model Works in Maricopa</h2>

  <p>
    The same three-person team serves you whether you visit our Buckeye headquarters or our Maricopa office. Brendan investigates. Brandon litigates. Stephanie guides you through every step.
  </p>

  <p>
    That structure means your case gets investigated before the insurance company starts building their defense. While other firms are still doing intake paperwork, Brendan is already at the crash scene documenting evidence.
  </p>

  <h2>Serving the Growing Maricopa Community</h2>

  <p>
    Maricopa has grown from a small desert community into a city of over 60,000. The Provinces, Rancho El Dorado, Cobblestone Farms, and the newer developments near Sorrento and Glennwilde are bringing young families into a community that's still building its infrastructure.
  </p>

  <p>
    More residents mean busier roads. Busier roads mean more crashes. We're here now because the community needs local representation that understands both Pinal County law and the specific conditions that cause injuries in Maricopa.
  </p>

  <h2>Get Started Today</h2>

  <p>
    Call <a href="tel:+16026540202">(602) 654-0202</a> or visit our Maricopa office for a free consultation. Most residents get a same-day or next-day appointment. If you can't come to us, we'll come to you.
  </p>
</PracticeAreaLayout>
